ðŸ§µ Java Thread States (Simplified)
New Thread is created but not started yet.

Ready-to-run

Thread is ready but waiting for CPU time (scheduler will decide).

Running

Thread is currently executing.

Non-runnable states (paused temporarily):

ðŸ”¹ Sleeping: Thread is paused for a set time (e.g., Thread.sleep()).

ðŸ”¹ Blocked for join completion: Waiting for another thread to finish (using join()).

ðŸ”¹ Blocked for I/O (highlighted): Waiting for I/O operation (e.g., file/network) to complete.

ðŸ”¹ Waiting for notification: Waiting for a signal (wait() method).

ðŸ”¹ Blocked for lock acquisition: Waiting to enter a synchronized block/method.

Dead

Thread has finished execution or terminated.

